   In ages past, there existed a powerful weapon in the neverending
battle against evil. This weapon was forged by the angels of
Mitra so that it could be used by any champion who desired to
combat evil, be that champion a mage, a warrior, a cleric or any
other calling.

   There were those, however, that sought the destruction of this
powerful weapon. Foremost among these was Thanatos, the Hater of
Life. Through craft and force he wrested the rod away from mortal
hands and cast it into the Mouth of Hell, a legendary volcano whose
eruption is said to mark the beginning of Armageddon. If this is
true, then Armageddon is upon us, for the volcano erupted seven days
later. Lava and ash rained down throughout the world. So ended the
Rod of the Seven Worlds.

   Or so the world thought for many centuries. Then, a piece of the
rod was found by a simple peasant in the village of Glaverton in
Glavia. Before more could be learned, however, Glaverton was over-
run by demons and the piece was lost. Perhaps if the Glavia piece
could be found, it might lead to the location of the remaining parts
of the ancient artifact.

Game Notes: There can only be one Rod of the Seven Worlds in
            existence at any one time.
Before you begin a lengthy quest you would be well-advised to take
some digging implements with you (perhaps a pick and shovel).
Some gnomes have recently begun work on the foreboding fortress.
Maybe one of them would be willing you loan you a shovel if you
ask nicely.
